How to visualize pore scafold by Paraview version 5.9.0

1. 	import bd_v3.4.2/anlys/vtk/pore_bcs.vtk

2. 	Clip
	- Clip Type: Cylinder
	- Center: 	(0,0,20)
	- Axis: 	(0,0,1)
	- Radius: 	20 (= R_pore)
	- Invert: 	uncheck



Other:

mesh screen shot
	- fg.vtk > Glyph: color = #007fb1 to #c9bc9c
	  orientation, scale = no array
	- clip (front): opacity 0.15
	- clip (top  ): opacity 0.5
	- screenshot: 1012 * 1348

trajectory screen shot
	- fg.vtk: line width = 1, color = #007fb1
	- fg.vtk > Glyph: color = #007fb1 to #c9bc9c
	  orientation, scale = no array
	- cg_ctr.vtk > pathline: line width = 5
	- animation: sequence, no.frames = 335 (oridinal is 670)
	- screenshot: 2000 * 2488

